snippet.textDisplay: I had always wondered how Dropout had stayed alive this long and I say this as a Dropout subscriber. But I also wonder how many of Drawfee's subscribers have a Dropout subscription (the best way to support them). If even 10% of us had a Dropout subscription, that'd be $675,000 a month in revenue ($5 per month). Per year that'd be over $8 million in revenue which surely would keep a small platform like Dropout afloat even with their employees located in expensive cities like NYC and SF. And that's just 10% of this channel, not including their other IPs or investors.

snippet.textDisplay:
Thank you guys, for bringing us all so much joy with your content. I don't know what I would do if this layoff were the end of Drawfee.
College Humor was one of the first channels I had ever heard of on YouTube back in 2005(ish) and I just thought it was the funniest thing ever.
Then, about 12 years later, my girlfriend showed me Drawfee and her "selling point" was the fact that Drawfee was a part of College Humor, and it got me to watch that first video of silly people making silly drawings. Since watching that video I've been inspired by you guys to dabble in my own drawings even though they're just absolutely awful. But they're fun and they bring me joy, which is what making any kind of art is all about.
I love you guys, and can't be happier to hear that you're going to keep moving forward with the channel in whatever manner possible. I'm sure that all of us really appreciate it. I know I do.
snippet.textOriginal:
Thank you guys, for bringing us all so much joy with your content. I don't know what I would do if this layoff were the end of Drawfee.
College Humor was one of the first channels I had ever heard of on YouTube back in 2005(ish) and I just thought it was the funniest thing ever.
Then, about 12 years later, my girlfriend showed me Drawfee and her "selling point" was the fact that Drawfee was a part of College Humor, and it got me to watch that first video of silly people making silly drawings. Since watching that video I've been inspired by you guys to dabble in my own drawings even though they're just absolutely awful. But they're fun and they bring me joy, which is what making any kind of art is all about.
I love you guys, and can't be happier to hear that you're going to keep moving forward with the channel in whatever manner possible. I'm sure that all of us really appreciate it. I know I do.
